Package com.hp.jipp.encoding

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Attribute<T>
    An IPP attribute, composed of a one-byte "value tag" suggesting its type, a human-readable string name, and one or more values according to its type.
    AttributeCollection
    The collection of attributes found within a class CollectionType attribute.
    AttributeGroup
    A specific group of attributes found in a packet.
    AttributeType<T>
    Associates a specific tag and name such that an attribute can be safely created or retrieved from a group
    BooleanType
    A boolean attribute type
    CollectionType
    A type for attribute collections.
    Encoder<T>
    Reads/writes attribute values
    Enum
    A machine-readable integer code paired with a human-readable name.
    EnumType<T extends Enum>
    An IPP enum type
    IntegerType
    Attribute type for Int attributes. May also encode an enum type if it is not recognized.
    IppInputStream  
    IppOutputStream  
    KeyValueType
    Attribute type for Key/Value pairs
    Keyword
    A known sequence of characters.
    KeywordOrNameType<T extends Keyword>
    Attribute type for attributes based on class Keyword or a simple string name
    KeywordType<T extends Keyword>
    Attribute type for attributes based on class Keyword
    LangString
    A string, possibly encoded with language
    LangStringType
    An language-encoded string attribute type
    OctetStringType
    An class AttributeType for octet string values (binary data)
    RangeOfIntegerType
    Attribute type for IntRange attributes
    Resolution
    Describes a printing resolution.
    ResolutionType
    Attribute type for encoding of a class Resolution
    ResolutionUnit
    A unit of measurement used to describe resolution
    SimpleEncoder<T>
    An encoder for simple values
    StringType
    An attribute bearing a string for which language is irrelevant.
    Tag
    Value and delimiter tags as specified by RFC2910 and RFC3382
    UriType
    An class AttributeType for URI attributes
